    GROUP_CONF="Group1 Group2 Group3" // single string of names separated by single space. Merlin cannot work on big pedigree. Thus, the data have to be split in several group, designed by this parameter. Example: GROUP_CONF="Group1 Group2 Group3". The group name will be used to name directories and must be a single string
    //GROUP_CONF=["Group1", "Group2", "Group3"] // single string of names separated by single space. Merlin cannot work on big pedigree. Thus, the data have to be split in several group, designed by this parameter. Example: GROUP_CONF="Group1 Group2 Group3". The group name will be used to name directories and must be a single string
